    "Specifically, we extract all search queries issued by the model (identified by search protocol tokens in the generated text) and count the number of valid, non-empty queries.",
    "The reward is computed as the ratio of the number of searches performed to an upper bound (set to 3 in our experiments), capped at 1.0.",
    "This design incentivizes the model to conduct multiple searches to gather diverse information sources, while preventing unbounded reward accumulation.",
    "Beyond rubric-based and citation-specific rewards, we introduce lightweight auxiliary rewards that encourage structural correctness of responses with respect to the expected output schema.",
